{"title_page": "Drona (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian Kannada-language action drama film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Drona\n| image          = Drona film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Release poster\n| director       = Pramod Chakravarthy\n| producer       = Mahadevappa B. Halagatthi\n| story          =  \n| starring       = [[Shiva Rajkumar]] <br /> [[Ravi Kishan]] <br/> [[Ineya]] <br/> [[Rangayana Raghu]]  \n| music          = Ramkrish\n| cinematography =  \n| editing        =  \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2020|03|06}}\n| runtime        = 122 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/drona/movie-review/74508613.cms|title=Drona Movie Review: This commercial film gets too preachy at times.|website=Times of India|date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n| studio         = Dolphin Media House\n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| budget         = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Drona''''' is a 2020 Indian [[Kannada]]-language [[Action film|action]] [[drama]] film, directed by Pramod Chakravarthy and produced by Mahadevappa B. Halagatthi under the banner Dolphin Media House. Starring [[Shiva Rajkumar]] playing the role of a government school teacher who fights for the survival of school.<ref name=toi>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/shivarajkumars-drona-to-release-on-march-6/articleshow/74253035.cms|title=Shivarajkumar's Drona to release on March 6|website=Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/from-drona-to-maduve-madri-sari-hogtane-kannada-movies-releasing-this-week/photostory/74495618.cms |title = From 'Drona' to 'Maduve Madri Sari Hogtane': Kannada movies releasing this week|date = 2020-03-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/puneeth-rajkumar-to-launch-drona-trailer-on-february-23/articleshow/74206478.cms |title = Puneeth Rajkumar to launch 'Drona' trailer on February 23? - Times of India}}</ref> The movie is an official remake of the 2012 Tamil movie ''[[Saattai]]''.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.timesofindia.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/drona/amp_movie_review/74508613.cms |title = Drona Movie Review, Trailer, & Show timings at Times of India Mobile}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nGuru ([[Shiva Rajkumar]])  an simpel government teacher whose purpose of life is to bring government schools on par with the private schools. When he is transferred to a government school in Nelamangala, he investigate and understand the problems that such institutions face. From teachers to politicians to students, and even the wards\u2019 parents, nobody wants any changes in the system. But Guru is annoyed by the mediocrity. \nPoliticians and teachers want to milk as much money as they can with each passing year from the government school. After getting a detail about this, Guru decides to change the system. \n\nAssistant Headmaster Raghu ([[Rangayana Raghu]]), a relative of the local politician Uday Krishna ([[Ravi Kishan]]), tries to create problems for him as he (Guru) stands between them and the school. How he overcomes the problems and wins the hearts of students and teachers forms the heart of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Shiva Rajkumar]] as Guru / Drona\n* [[Ravi Kishan]] as Uday Krishna\n* [[Ineya]] \n* [[Rangayana Raghu]] as Raghu (Assistant Headmaster)\n* Swati Sharma\n* V Manohar \n* [[Sadhu Kokila]] \n* Babu Hiranya \n* [[Rekha Das]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Drona\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| 