d by the mediocrity. \nPoliticians and teachers want to milk as much money as they can with each passing year from the government school. After getting a detail about this, Guru decides to change the system. \n\nAssistant Headmaster Raghu ([[Rangayana Raghu]]), a relative of the local politician Uday Krishna ([[Ravi Kishan]]), tries to create problems for him as he (Guru) stands between them and the school. How he overcomes the problems and wins the hearts of students and teachers forms the heart of the story.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Shiva Rajkumar]] as Guru / Drona\n* [[Ravi Kishan]] as Uday Krishna\n* [[Ineya]] \n* [[Rangayana Raghu]] as Raghu (Assistant Headmaster)\n* Swati Sharma\n* V Manohar \n* [[Sadhu Kokila]] \n* Babu Hiranya \n* [[Rekha Das]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Drona\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Ramkrish \n| cover      =\n| border     = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 24 February 2020\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 16:47\n| label      = Anand Audio\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External media\n| audio1     = {{YouTube|0LDX-fr9zDc|Audio Jukebox}}}}\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack composed by Ramkrish with lyrics from Dr. V Nagendra Prasad, Phanish Raj and Arasu Anthare.\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline      = Track listing\n| total_length  = 16:47\n| extra_column  = Singer(s)\n| title1   = Sri Raamane\n| extra1   = Swaravijayi, [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| lyrics1  = Dr. V. Nagendra Prasad\n| length1  =  05:12\n\n| title2   = Shake Ma Sainora\n| extra2   = [[Sanjith Hegde]]\n| lyrics2  = Phanish Raj\n| length2  = 03:43\n\n| title3   = Mirri Mirriyaa\n| extra3   = Chethan Naik, Priya Mali\n| lyrics3  = Phanish Raj\n| length3  = 02:21\n\n| title4   = Neenu Mechokaage\n| extra4   = Priya Mali\n| lyrics4  = Phanish Raj\n| length4  = 02:08 \n\n| title5   = Guru Brahma\n| extra5   = Dr